correctness.rationale: Major factual and schema issues across all three processes. Key problems: (1) Unit errors: Growth-per-cycle values are off by 10× because article reports 0.13/0.07/0.10 nm per cycle (≈1.3/0.7/1.0 Å), but extraction uses 0.13/0.07/0.10 Å. Dosing/purge times are given in milliseconds but numeric values correspond to seconds; should be 16000/50000/15000 ms (etc.), not 16/50/15. (2) Inconsistencies: Film thicknesses (28.3, 24.6, 27.7 nm) are paired with 30 cycles, whereas the article ties these thicknesses to 200, 350, and 270 cycles, respectively. (3) Unsupported/fabricated values: Reactor pressure (50 mmHg), all flow rates (100 sccm), optical properties (n, absorption), band gap with Tauc method, electrical properties (resistivity, carrier density, mobility), device properties (μ_FE, V_T, SS, I_ON/I_OFF), uniformity, conformality, roughness, and statements on film stability/reproducibility are not reported in the article. (4) Partial process description: For the WpO process, only a single co-reactant dosing time is provided; the additional O2 plasma pulse (8 s) is missing from dosing/purge timing. (5) Schema violations/misuse: plasmaPower is set to null in the TALD process (should be omitted if not used); filmThickness is incorrectly nested under growthPerCycle (not allowed by schema); dosing/purge time units use MilliSEC but with second-scale numbers; reactor manufacturer listed as “CN1 Atomic Premium” is a tool model, not a manufacturer. (6) Minor but notable: filmDensity method labeled as ellipsometry, whereas densities were derived from HR-RBS areal density plus thickness; safety claim “not pyrophoric” is not explicitly stated for this precursor in the article. Corrections needed: fix GPC to 1.3/0.7/1.0 Å; express all pulse/purge times in correct units (ms) with correct numeric values; align number of cycles with the reported thicknesses (200/350/270) or adjust thicknesses to match 30-cycle data; remove or mark as not reported all unsupported parameters (pressure, flows, optical/electrical/device/uniformity/conformality/roughness); add O2 plasma dosing time for WpO; remove null plasmaPower and the improperly nested filmThickness; adjust filmDensity method attribution; avoid unsubstantiated safety/reproducibility claims.

completeness.rationale: Three distinct ZnO ALD processes (pO, W, WpO) are captured with correct precursor, oxidants, reactor type, temperature (200 °C), plasma power (100 W for plasma steps), Ar carrier/purge, and qualitative findings (no nucleation delay, stoichiometric films). However, multiple inaccuracies, missing details, and schema issues reduce completeness: (1) Growth-per-cycle values are off by 10×: article reports 0.13/0.07/0.10 nm/cycle (≈1.3/0.7/1.0 Å), but extraction uses 0.13/0.07/0.10 Å. (2) Dosing and purge times are given with MilliSEC units but numeric values are in seconds; they should be converted (e.g., 16 s → 16000 ms; 50 s → 50000 ms; 15 s purge → 15000 ms; WpO requires both 15 s H2O and 8 s O2 plasma dosing times—only one co-reactant time is provided). (3) Number of cycles is incorrect/inconsistent: 30 cycles are listed while film thicknesses (28.3, 24.6, 27.7 nm) correspond to ~200/350/270 cycles reported; update numberofCycles per process accordingly. (4) Reactor pressure and all flow rates are not reported in the article; values (e.g., 50 mTorr, 100 sccm) are unsupported. (5) Many material/device properties (refractive index, absorption, electrical properties, uniformity, conformality, roughness, device metrics) are not provided in the paper and should not be populated with fabricated values. (6) Schema-related issues: in the thermal (W) process, plasmaPower is set to null (should be omitted, not null); WpO dosing lacks the second co-reactant timing; filmThickness is duplicated at processParameters level (potentially outside defined properties). Properties to review/correct: growthPerCycle units/values, dosingTime and purgeTime units and completeness (include 8 s O2 plasma in WpO), numberofCycles per process, remove or justify pressure/flow values, remove unsupported material/device properties or replace with traceable values, and fix schema compliance (omit null plasmaPower, resolve filmThickness placement).
